eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 20 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Patients who have received prior treatment with an mTOR inhibitor (sirolimus, temsirolimus, everolimus)

groups.description: Patients receive cabozantinib-s-malate PO QD on days 1-28. Courses repeat every 28 days in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (cabozantinib-s-malate)

groups.description: Patients receive BCG intravesical solution weekly in weeks 1-6 and 15-17 and tremelimumab IV over 1 hour in weeks 3 and 15.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (biological therapy and monoclonal antibody)

outcome_measures.measure: Frequency and severity of toxicity incidents assessed by Common Terminology Criteria version 2.0

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Maximum grade over all courses will be used as the summary measure per patient.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of non-hematologic and hematologic toxicities, as measured by NCI Common Toxicity Criteria, version 4.0
